Gemini is still learning, and it gets help from Google Assistant for some actions. When Google Assistant helps out, some Google Assistant settings apply, like personal results and Google Assistant on lock screen. You can manage these in Gemini Settings.

When Gemini handles actions through Extensions, Google Assistant settings for personal results, lock screen, and calendar won’t apply. Your Gemini Apps activity will be used to help with actions requests, like to select a frequent contact or app. To help you get started, Gemini will import the last 90 days of Google Assistant communications history from your Web & App Activity to Gemini Apps Activity.

Other assistive features for your device outside of your Gemini mobile app (like navigation experiences) may be directly powered by Google Assistant. Learn more about how Gemini & Google Assistant work together on your device

The northern lights, also known as the aurora borealis, are a natural light display predominantly seen in high-latitude regions around the Arctic. They appear as curtains, rays, spirals, or dynamic flickers covering the entire sky in brilliant colors, most commonly pale green and pink, but also shades of red, yellow, blue, and violet.

The northern lights are formed when electrically charged particles from the Sun collide with Earth’s atmosphere. These collisions excite the atoms in the atmosphere, causing them to release energy in the form of light. The color of the light depends on the type of gas atom that is excited.
The northern lights are a beautiful and awe-inspiring natural phenomenon. They are a reminder of the power and majesty of the universe.
